<Author>Frenchbantam
<Content>Gret Hotel In Florence I have just returned from 2 nights at the Montebello Splendid in Florence. Overall the hotel is excellent and a great base for exploring Tuscany. We stayed in the Family Duplex Room as there were 3 adults. The room was very spacious, well appointed and the beds are very comfortable. The bathroom is very good with an excellent shower over the bath. The staff were very pleasant and helpful. We asked for restaurant recommendations each night and both were excellent choices. We like to eat where the locals do and enjoyed fabulous food. The breakfast buffet was very good with both hold and cold choices. The champagne on offer was a nice touch. The hotel is situated about 15 minutes walk from the centre of Florence and it is a pleasant walk along the river. We all love Florence and have now found a perfect place to stay for future visits. 
