<Author>TexasWill56
<Content>Loved the hotel My wife and I just returned from a fabulous trip to Florence, Italy. We went there as a side detour of a business trip that I had to Germany. We called it our early 30th anniversary celebration vacation. We stayed at the Montebello Splendid hotel and we loved it. The hotel is fairly new, circa 2004, but it was built and decorated in traditional Italian style with antiques, hardwood floors, marble bathrooms, plus jacuzzi, LCD TV, and fully automated room controls. The room was plenty big enough for all our gear and included 2 nice arm chairs and a table which are in addition to the TV/computer desk, unlike many rooms in Europe which tend to be tiny. We had booked a standard double but the hotel upgraded us to a deluxe double including a balconcy with table and chairs for free of charge. The staff was very helpful and friendly and always available. They even pre-arranged reserved tickets for us to a couple of the museums in Florence. The breakfast buffet was excellent with a wide variety. The hotel and the rooms were 1st class and we look forward to staying there again if we ever get to go back. 
