<Author>goddot08
<Content>Luxurious room with excellent breakfast My husband and I stayed at Montebello Splendid for two nights during our honeymoon in July. We booked a standard room and were upgraded to a beautiful junior suite. The room has a spacious bedroom with a queen bed, a small living area, and a bathroom with shower (no bath tub though). The AC keeps the room comfortably cool when it's steaming hot outside. The buffet breakfast is excellent with a wide selection of egg, bacon, sausage, cold meat, pastry, cereal, yogurt, fruits, and cheese. The sun-lit breakfast room, friendly server, and free copy of USA Today (newspaper) set a relaxed atmosphere to start a day.The fee for a cab ride to the Florence Airport as well as the train station is quite reasonable ( 20 Euro). The only minus is the location - the hotel is about 15 minutes walk to major sights. However it's not a problem for us as we love strolling along the Arno River. The room has no river view. (In comparison, Grand Hotel and Westin Excelsior are located by the Arno River. I considered those two hotels when booking but preferred the more modern Montebello Splendid.) The reception staff is friendly, but not overly enthusiastic in recommending tourist spots. Overall, a pleasant stay in a romantic hotel for a good price. We wish we could stay there longer! Pros: Luxurious suite, excellent breakfast, good value Cons: No view, slightly far away from major sights 
