<Content>Cosmopolitan Luxury in the heart of Florence Staying at the Montebello Splendid is like being a guest at your rich aunt's in-the-city estate. The layout, with the courtyard and fountain, indoor/outdoor dining room, high quality stone construction, reinforce this home vs. hotel appeal. Indoors, the rooms and common areas are all richly appointed with marble, elegant furniture, art works, etc. Breakfast consisted of the standard Eurpoean items, but quality was a step above other hotels. Staff was helpful ... but I would not say more so than at the other decent hotels that we stayed at in Italy. The top attractions are within walking distance (Duomo, Ufizzi, Ponte Vechio), as is the main train station. But understand that by walking I mean 20 - 30 minute strolls, along the scenic river, or on pleasant neighborhood streets. That may sound like a long walk, but when included in the hours and hours of walking and standing that you will do at the musems, churches, shopping areas, etc, its just part of the vacation experience. The rooms in the Montebello have super comfortable beds, with nice linens. Lots of high tech electronics .. remote light switches  shutter controls, flat panel tv, high speed internet, etc. Bathroom overall was very nice, but the shower has a design defect, that causes the floor near it to get wet every time the shower is used. Just accept it ... what's a little wet marble anyway. Overall it was just the extra treat we wanted to have during the Florence leg of our multi-city vacation. 
