<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>My home away from home After staying at five stars in Rome, Siena, (de Russie, Hassler, and the Grand Continental) I have to say that Montebello holds its own for one third of the price. A wonderful half hour walk (remember you are on the vacation and need to burn the carbs you are ingesting), this hotel provided a sanctuary away from the hustle and bustle of downtown Florence. The staff provided a warm and welcome reception although it appeared at first to the hotel seemed to have been deserted when I arrived. Despite first impressions, I simply adore the two Francos at the concierge desk who made all of my reservations at the Uffizi and for dinner. I felt like a royal princess here. Great bath and supplies; breakfast was excellent in comparison to other places where an American breakfast like this served went for 29 Euros. What made it taste better is that it was included in the price of the room. Luxury and comfort ( the most comfortable of all beds on my trip). My first room was a little strange in that it had a series of steep steps leading up to the bathroom (loft type arrangement) -- I nearly killed myself going to the bathroom in the middle of the night when I missed the last two stairs, but upon my return from Siena to come back to see a friend in town, I was given a wonderful luxurious upgrade for the same $149 a night with breakfast included and without the strange stairs. What was terrific about this place is that I called the morning of my unanticipated return and Franco recognized my voice-- when I asked him about availabilityand whether they would assure the same expedia rate, he said that they were so happy that I was returning that of course they would keep a room for me.. From here on out -- this is the place i will stay regardless of the fact it is not a room with a view . As far as the inference that things were stolen in another reviewers review (see below) my experience was that all my belongings were safe here--- I never used the safe, left clothing and nearly 10,000 dollars worth of jewelry and clothes thrown around my room, never closed my suitcases and never missed one thing. The people i met at this hotel were wonderful. This is my home away from home when I am in Florence. 
